         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:ching2010"/><citedRange>140</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">The <hi>saṃgha</hi> of ?-<hi>ṣkuneke</hi> addresses his greetings to <hi>Nāri</hi> the General: Oh lord! (As) you know it fully (by your)-self, the monastery of (your) own father does (now) belong to you. ... ///</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a1 #a2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>710</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[Now], there is enlargement (of) the <hi>saṃgha</hi>. Likewise the artisans stay (here). They are working out scaffoldings(?) in order to (make?) <hi>Śimpraye</hi>'s window. You are lacking grain. [Now] ... ///</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Zudem sitzen die Handwerker [da] [und] arbeiten zum Fenster des Śimpraye hin an Söllern.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Furthermore, the craftsmen are sitting [there] [and are] working on balconies towards Śimpraye's window.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>502</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Euch fehlt es weit[hin] an Getreide.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">You [pl.] lack grain far [and wide].</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>109</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... we have great zeal. (lit. 'there is good zeal with us.') Now, we address to you in expectation: even in (the form of) a few grains, you should have done some advantage (for us)! In many other monasteries ... [advantage] (has been done). ///</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Here indeed, it is necessary for you to seek and take care of (lit. 'ask about') the good fortune (and) the suffering of the <hi>saṃgha</hi>, in the monastery established by <hi>Iśśapake</hi>. Now, in expectation, [we address] (in) [good] (manner) [to you] ... ///</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1 #b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">/// Gift/donation (is better to be) ten piculs of grain afterwards.</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Now we say well in confidence to you: «… as a gift finally 10 cāk of grain, so that it will be possible here in your power to create zeal and virtuousness for the community».</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>710</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">So that here indeed in your own power, the zeal of the <hi>saṃgha</hi> will be able to make/produce the side of virtue. Likewise/With ... ///</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2 #b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">/// will be made for/by you.</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
